## Factory Mode

When invoked with `/factory TICKET-{id}`:
- All human gates use auto-defaults
- Ticket readiness checked automatically (`/check-readiness`)
- Code standards validated locally -- **deployment handled by CI**
- PR gets `factory` label -> triggers CI workflows
- On halt: notify team, do not wait for user

### Pipeline

```
/draft-story (architect resolves questions)
    -> Ticket "Ready for Sprint"
    |
/factory TICKET-xxx
  |-- /check-readiness
  |-- Create worktree + branch
  |-- Scaffold + implement
  |-- /validate (code standards only)
  |-- Commit + PR (factory label) -> CI deploys -> reviewer tests -> merge -> deploy
```

## Common Development Commands

### Code Formatting & Linting

```bash
pnpm lint              # ESLint check (Next.js config + custom rules)
pnpm lint:fix          # ESLint auto-fix
pnpm format            # Prettier format all files
pnpm format:check      # Prettier check only (runs in CI)
pnpm typecheck         # TypeScript compiler check (no emit)
```

### Testing

```bash
pnpm test              # Run full test suite (Vitest)
pnpm test:unit         # Unit tests only
pnpm test:integration  # Integration tests (requires local DB)
pnpm test:e2e          # Playwright end-to-end tests
pnpm test:e2e:ui       # Playwright with UI mode for debugging
pnpm test:coverage     # Generate coverage report (lcov + text)
```

### Database

```bash
pnpm db:migrate        # Run pending Prisma migrations
pnpm db:seed           # Seed local database with sample data
pnpm db:reset          # Drop, recreate, migrate, and seed
pnpm db:studio         # Open Prisma Studio (GUI)
```

### Deployment

```bash
pnpm build             # Production build (runs typecheck + next build)
vercel --env preview   # Deploy preview branch to Vercel
# Production deploys happen automatically on merge to main via Vercel Git integration
```

## Development Guidelines

### Coding Standards

- Use camelCase for variables and functions, PascalCase for components and types
- All exported functions and components must have JSDoc comments
- Maximum function length: 40 lines; extract helpers for anything longer
- Prefer named exports over default exports (exception: Next.js page/layout files which require default exports)
- Use absolute imports with path aliases: `@/components`, `@/lib`, `@/types`
- No `any` type -- use `unknown` and narrow with type guards
- Colocate component files: `ComponentName/index.tsx`, `ComponentName.test.tsx`, `ComponentName.stories.tsx`
- Use `const` by default; `let` only when reassignment is necessary; never `var`
- Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when hooks or browser APIs are needed
- All string literals displayed to users must go through `next-intl` (i18n)

### Error Handling

- API routes return structured errors: `{ error: string, code: string, details?: object }`
- Use custom error classes extending `AppError` (defined in `src/lib/errors.ts`)
- All `try/catch` blocks must log with `logger.error()` including `requestId` and `userId` context
- Client-side errors caught by the global `error.tsx` boundary; per-route boundaries for critical flows (checkout, auth)
- Stripe webhook handlers must return 200 even on internal failure to prevent retries; log and enqueue for manual review
- Never expose internal error messages or stack traces to the client

### Testing Strategy

- **Unit tests** (Vitest): Required for all business logic in `src/lib/` -- minimum 80% line coverage
- **Component tests** (Vitest + Testing Library): Required for interactive UI components
- **Integration tests** (Vitest): API routes tested with `supertest` against a test database
- **E2E tests** (Playwright): Cover critical user flows -- sign-up, product browse, add-to-cart, checkout, subscription management
- Use factories in `tests/factories/` for test data -- never hardcode IDs, emails, or Stripe tokens
- Mock external services (Stripe, email) at the HTTP boundary using `msw`
- CI runs the full suite; PRs cannot merge if any test fails or coverage drops below threshold

## Code Organization

```
src/
  app/                    # Next.js App Router
    (store)/              # Public storefront route group
      page.tsx            # Homepage
      products/           # Product listing and detail pages
      cart/               # Shopping cart
      checkout/           # Checkout flow
    (auth)/               # Authentication routes (sign-in, sign-up, forgot-password)
    admin/                # Internal admin dashboard (protected)
    api/                  # API route handlers
      webhooks/           # Stripe and third-party webhook handlers
  components/
    ui/                   # Reusable UI primitives (Button, Modal, Input, Card, etc.)
    features/             # Feature-scoped components (ProductCard, CartDrawer, SubscriptionManager)
    layouts/              # Shared layout components (Header, Footer, Sidebar)
  lib/
    api/                  # API client helpers and typed fetch wrappers
    auth/                 # NextAuth.js configuration and utilities
    db/                   # Prisma client instance and query helpers
    errors.ts             # Custom error classes
    hooks/                # Custom React hooks
    stripe/               # Stripe SDK wrappers and helpers
    utils/                # Pure utility functions (formatting, validation, etc.)
  types/                  # Shared TypeScript types and interfaces
  styles/                 # Global CSS and Tailwind theme overrides
prisma/
  schema.prisma           # Database schema
  migrations/             # Migration history
  seed.ts                 # Database seed script
tests/
  unit/                   # Unit tests (mirrors src/lib/ structure)
  integration/            # API route integration tests
  e2e/                    # Playwright specs
  factories/              # Test data factories
  fixtures/               # Static test fixtures (images, JSON payloads)
```

## Version Control

### Branching Strategy

- **`main`** -- primary integration branch; always deployable
- **Feature branches** -- `TICKET-xxx` format, branched from `main`
- **Release branches** -- not used; we deploy continuously from `main`
- **Hotfix branches** -- `hotfix/TICKET-xxx`, branched from `main`, merged back immediately

### Pull Request Guidelines

- **Base branch**: `main`
- **PR title format**: `{Ticket-ID}: {Story Title}`
- **Assignee**: Always assign to yourself (`--assignee @me`)
- **Reviewers**: Minimum 1 approval required; auto-assigned via CODEOWNERS
- **CI gates**: Lint, typecheck, full test suite, Vercel preview build must all pass
- **Merge strategy**: Squash and merge; branch auto-deleted after merge
- **Draft PRs**: Use for work-in-progress to get early feedback

## Integrations

- **CI/CD**: GitHub Actions (workflows in `.github/workflows/`)
  - `ci.yml` -- lint, typecheck, test on every push
  - `e2e.yml` -- Playwright tests on PR against preview deployment
- **Hosting**: Vercel (auto-deploy preview on PR push, production on merge to `main`)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 15 on Vercel Postgres (dev uses local Docker container)
- **Payments**: Stripe (test mode keys in `.env.local`, production keys in Vercel env vars)
- **Auth**: NextAuth.js with Google and email/password providers
- **Monitoring**: Vercel Analytics + Sentry for error tracking (DSN in env vars)
- **Email**: Resend for transactional emails (order confirmation, password reset)
- **Image CDN**: Cloudinary for product images (transformations via URL params)
